EXP NO: 4				
LARGEST/SMALLEST FROM A SERIES USING 8051 TRAINER KIT

OBJECTIVE:
4.a To find the largest from a series

•	Read the count of the series (N) from memory location 4600H and store it in R1 register. 
•	Find the largest among the ‘N’ series of numbers starting from memory location 4601H and store the result in register R2.

4.b To find the smallest from a series

•	Read the count of the series (N) from memory location 4600H and store it in R1 register. 
•	Find the smallest among the ‘N’ series of number starting from memory location 4601H and store the result in register R2.

LEARNING OUTCOMES:
After completing this experiment, the students will be able to write and execute assembly language program to find the largest/smallest from a series using 8051 trainer kit.
EQUIPMENTS REQUIRED: 8051 trainer kit.          
THEORY:
To find the largest or smallest number from a given series, the data values are stored in memory locations and accessed sequentially using the 8051 microcontroller. The Accumulator (A) loads each element using a pointer register (R0/R1). Initially, the first element is assumed as the largest or smallest. The remaining elements are compared using the CJNE instruction, and based on the carry flag, the stored value is updated. A loop counter controls the number of comparisons. Finally, the result is stored in memory and verified on the 8051 Trainer Kit.
This experiment demonstrates comparison, looping, and memory addressing in the 8051.
